TH man 1 "14 June 2023" "1.0" "Grady Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
Grady - A friendly command-line interpreter for beginners and experienced users.

.SH SYNOPSIS
Grady

.SH DESCRIPTION
Grady shell is a command line interpreter that provides an environment for executing commands and  performing system operations. It reads and executes commands from standard input. Grady shell supports both built-in commands and external programs.

.SH STARTING THE PROGRAM
Once complied, to start the program, run:
./Grady$

.SH EXITING THE PROGRAM
To exit the program, run:
Grady $ exit

.SH COMMANDS
The following commands are supported by Grady shell:

.PP
.B cd[directory]
Change the current working directory

.PP
.B pwd
Print the current working directory

.PP
.B echo[arguments..]
Display the given arguments

.SH PIPELINES
Grady shell supports command pipelines, allowing for the chaining of multiple commands. the output of one command is used as the input for the next command in the pipeline.

.SH BUILT-INS
The following built-ins are supported by the Grady shell

.B env -
Print the current environment

.B setenv VARIABLE VALVUE -
Initialize a new environment variable, or modify an existing one.

.B unsetenv VARIABLE -
Remove an environment variable.

.SH RETURN VALUES
The Grady shell program returns the following exit status values:
.PP
.B 0
Successful execution

.PP
.B Non-zero
An error occurred during execution

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH AUTHOR
Grady shell was developed by Dorothy Dede Quao(dorothyokoto@gmail.com) and Grace Amaning-Kwarteng(graceamaningkwarteng@gmail.com)
